This paper deals with security and protection of enclaves in a system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of the defense in hardware and software, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE) respectively. The paper also mentions the use of Intel SGX, which is related to computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the performance overhead of the defense, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) as it relates to optimizing code for performance.
